history.text: Hello!
Have you seen Zootopia?
Yes I have!
I really like the Character Judy the bunny and her strive to be a police officer even though she is a small rabbit.
Yes I agree she was really determined to prove to herself that she could do anything she set out to do.
Yeah, and I liked the hidden message to look passed stereotypes
What do you think about Duke Weaselton?
He is a key character too, how about that sheep  Jenny slate, the assistant mayor?
Yeah she definitely played a key part in Judy making the choices that she did.
I think we're supposed two have 3 turns right? I could talk about Zootopia longer thou it's a very funny movie we enjoy the smart humor at our house and we've seen it many times.
I believe it might be on a 30-minute timer but I am not sure. I agree that it is a funny movie they do a good job of teaching valuable lessons to kids while also making it good for adults to watch.
I just looked, we each need to take 12 turns
I agree it was good for adults and kids. I really like the back and fourth with Judy and Nick, how she tricked him into working with him because of his tax evasion. Ha Ha!
I thought it was cool when Judy asked Nick if he wanted to be a partner because they worked well together.
Yes they did, Nick also stood up for Judy like a real friend when he reminded Chief bogo thet she still had time remaining to solve the case.
It was entertaining when they replaced the gun so it would have blueberries in it haha
That was sly, He really trusted her by revealing that he was bullied as a kid, my romantic heart wished for a romance.
What did you think about the ending to the movie?
That was funny, I'm glad they we're able to work together after the insults at the press conference.
Yeah I agree it was definitely an interesting part of the film.
I really thought she was going to quit for good after she left her job at the police force.
It would have probably been a smart choice
The movie seemed to get good reviews, 98% by Rotten tomatoes and on average 8/10 liked it. Honestly I feel like it should be higher. It was really smart and cute.
Yeah I agree but a 98% is very high and I don't think it could go much higher that is one of the best ratings I have ever seen.
That scene in the natural History Museum was tricky with the serum pellets replaced with blueberries.
Yeah I thought he was going to catch on to it before they could do it.
yeah, and then Judy records Bellwether with her same carrot trick getting her arrested.
Would you like to see another Zootopia movie made?
Yes, I would definitely watch a sequel Maybe Judy and Nick will be an item
Great! It was nice talking to you about the movie! Have a nice night
you too

uid1response.feedback: We both agreed that it was a great movie.
